ost modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth de Poynings was born in 1349, in Sussex, England, her father, Michael de Poynings, was 31 and her mother, Joane de Rokesley, was 28. She married John de Grey Baron Grey about 1354. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in February 1368, in Slaugham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 19."},"et":{"1349–February 1368":"1349–veebruar 1368","1349–1375":"1349–1375","1349–1368":"1349–1368","1350–1403":"1350–1403","1351–1383":"1351–1383","1355–1387":"1355–1387","1345–1375":"1345–1375","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1356–1396":"1356–1396","1365–1448":"1365–1448","1318–1369":"1318–1369","1321–1369":"1321–1369","before 1348":"enne 1348","1396":"1396","1351":"1351","1383":"1383","1350":"1350","1349":"1349","1448":"1448","1403":"1403","1369":"1369","1368":"1368","1356":"1356","1345":"1345","1355":"1355","1365":"1365","1321":"1321","1387":"1387","1375":"1375","about 1354":"umbes 1354","February 1368":"veebruar 1368","1318":"1318","Ryedale, Yorkshire, England":"Ryedale, Yorkshire, England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","Slaugham, Sussex, England":"Slaugham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rycote, Oxfordshire, England":"Rycote, Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1349–February 1368":"1349–helmikuu 1368","1349–1375":"1349–1375","1349–1368":"1349–1368","1350–1403":"1350–1403","1351–1383":"1351–1383","1355–1387":"1355–1387","1345–1375":"1345–1375","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","1356–1396":"1356–1396","1365–1448":"1365–1448","1318–1369":"1318–1369","1321–1369":"1321–1369","before 1348":"ennen vuotta 1348","1396":"1396","1351":"1351","1383":"1383","1350":"1350"